Current documentation on [Generating Thread Dump|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Generating+a+Thread+Dump] include limited option. 

The documentation should also include Jvisualvm as another option that can be use in all Operating System.  

Especially for [JIRA installed using the Archive Files|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Installing+JIRA+from+an+Archive+File+on+Windows,+Linux+or+Solaris] , Jvisualvm can be use to generate the thread dump with the assumption that the JIRA server has JAVA_HOME configured.

To generate the thread dump using Jvisualvm:
# check the Process ID for JIRA Application.
** in Linux this can be confirmed by executing the command
{code}
ps -ef | grep java
{code}
** in Windows, this can checked in Task Manager
# navigate to the {{$JAVA_HOME/bin}} directory
# execute jvisualvm command/
** in Linux run the command {{jvisualvm}}
** in Windows run the command {{jvisualvm.exe}}
# in JVisualVm , right click on the JIRA's Process ID and the option to generate thread dump will be shown. (i) clicking on the "Thread Dump" will generate one thread dump
# to save the generated thread dump, right click on the thread dump generated and select "Save"

